  "prompt": "Is there a website where I can watch Broadway musical videos for free?",
  "response": "Watching Broadway musicals legally and for free can be challenging, as most official platforms require payment or a subscription. However, there are some legitimate options to explore:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Some Broadway productions or theater companies upload clips, behind-the-scenes content, or promotional videos for free. You can also find recorded performances of older or lesser-known shows, though these may not always be authorized.\n\n2. **The Shows Must Go On!**: During the COVID-19 pandemic, Andrew Lloyd Webber\u2019s production company released full-length musicals for free on YouTube for a limited time. While they no longer offer full shows regularly, they occasionally release special events.\n\n3. **BroadwayHD Free Trial**: BroadwayHD is a subscription service that streams Broadway shows. They often offer a free trial period (usually 7 days), which you can use to watch musicals for free before committing to a subscription.\n\n4. **Local Libraries**: Some libraries offer free access to streaming services like Kanopy or Hoopla, which may include filmed versions of Broadway musicals.\n\n5. **National Theatre at Home**: While not strictly Broadway, the National Theatre in London occasionally streams high-quality productions for free on YouTube or through their platform.\n\nAlways ensure you\u2019re using legitimate sources to support the artists and creators behind these productions. Avoid unauthorized or pirated content, as it undermines the theater industry.",
